        <div class="container" style="padding: 70px 0; left:20px;">
          <h1 class="title is-size-10" style="font-weight: 700;">
            About the API
          </h1>
          <br>
          <p class="subtitle" style="color:#858482">
            The NYPD Car Crashes dataset contains all of the reports of car accidents happended in New York City. The API we built included the car crashes happend from 2016 to March 2022.
            This API only includes the crashes that caused injuries. For each row of data, there are geographical data, including latitute and longitude of the crash, the coordinate of the intersection 
            the crash happened, and the street names; the date, time, and the day of week it happended; and details of the crash like major causes and the category of the road users.
          </p>
          <br>
          <p class="subtitle" style="color:#858482">
            Using the data from this API, we can create a safty notification map for users to know whether there are dangerous intersections along their iteneraries, so they could avoid them or stay alert.
            We can also create a data dashboard for the policy makers, using machine learning algorithms and with the integration of other datasets, to find out where in this city could have a high chance of
            having car crashes in the near future. 
          </p>
          <a class="button button-white is-medium is-success is-outlined" href="/route"> Map Demo </a>
          <br>
